HEADWORD: Epizeuxis
<hw>Ep`i*zeux"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/ a fastening together, repetition, fr. <?/ to fasten to or upon;
<grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <?/ to join, yoke.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A figure by which a word is repeated with vehemence or emphasis, as
in the following lines: --</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><examp>Alone</examp>, <examp>alone</examp>, <examp>all all
alone</examp>,⟦br⟧
<examp>Alone</examp> on a <examp>wide wide</examp> sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

